00:38:41.640 --> 00:38:43.410
Come on. Damienne.

715
00:38:43.470 --> 00:38:45.880
Don't get the keys mixed up.

716
00:38:45.910 --> 00:38:49.420
Remember. your air supply
inside your chamber is limited.

717
00:38:49.490 --> 00:38:52.090
- Stay calm!
- My heart is pumping.

718
00:38:52.120 --> 00:38:53.530
I'm struggling for air.

719
00:38:53.560 --> 00:38:55.800
I'm trying to find
the right key.

720
00:38:55.800 --> 00:38:58.900
- I'm feeling trapped.
- Oh. man. This is close.

721
00:38:58.900 --> 00:39:04.380
None of these
keys are working!

722
00:39:04.410 --> 00:39:06.990
Go. go!

723
00:39:11.200 --> 00:39:16.870
- Come on!
- - None of these keys are working!

724
00:39:16.870 --> 00:39:18.410
Oh. man. This is close.

725
00:39:18.440 --> 00:39:19.980
Come on!

726
00:39:20.050 --> 00:39:22.990
- You got it. girl.
- You got it. baby. You got it.

727
00:39:23.050 --> 00:39:25.990
- She got the lock off.
- Come on! Open it. Open it.

728
00:39:26.060 --> 00:39:28.430
- Get the chain off!
Get the chain off!
- Open it!

729
00:39:28.430 --> 00:39:30.840
Now press the button!
Come on!

730
00:39:32.510 --> 00:39:33.340
Johnny:
Now Zach got the lock off.

731
00:39:33.610 --> 00:39:35.940
- Damienne. push! Hurry up!
- It's neck and neck!

732
00:39:38.580 --> 00:39:40.820
- Yeah! Yes!
- Zach got it.

733
00:39:44.600 --> 00:39:45.830
Whoa!

734
00:39:45.870 --> 00:39:47.700
- Oh. my gosh.
- Johnny: That was so close.

735
00:39:47.740 --> 00:39:49.710
- Oh. my God.
- ...kidding me.

736
00:39:49.710 --> 00:39:52.710
Johnny: Damienne actually
got the lock off first.

737
00:39:52.750 --> 00:39:54.850
but Zach got out first.

738
00:39:54.850 --> 00:39:58.960
and he beat Damienne
to the button by
a fraction of a second.

739
00:40:00.290 --> 00:40:02.970
- No way.
- Wow. that was--

740
00:40:03.030 --> 00:40:06.740
that was so close.

741
00:40:06.810 --> 00:40:09.480
Don't matter.
You showed up and
showed out. baby.

742
00:40:09.480 --> 00:40:11.520
- That was crazy. That was--
- You did that. girl.

743
00:40:11.520 --> 00:40:13.850
- You showed up and showed the out.
- - Good job. Damienne.

744
00:40:13.850 --> 00:40:15.590
Damienne.
you fought really hard.

745
00:40:15.620 --> 00:40:18.500
You got out of your
jacket so quick.

746
00:40:18.560 --> 00:40:21.200
And you have...

747
00:40:24.580 --> 00:40:26.480
- Sorry.
- Mm.

748
00:40:26.480 --> 00:40:28.450
Oh. that hurts. bro.

749
00:40:29.650 --> 00:40:31.050
You done really good.

750
00:40:32.790 --> 00:40:35.530
- You beat me. for sure.
- It's not about you right now.

751
00:40:35.600 --> 00:40:36.970
- It's not about you.
- Okay.

752
00:40:38.240 --> 00:40:40.240
- We're all going to miss you.
- Yep.

753
00:40:40.310 --> 00:40:42.680
Man.

754
00:40:42.680 --> 00:40:44.850
Um...

755
00:40:45.650 --> 00:40:47.520
I know tonight.
fear was a factor.

756
00:40:47.590 --> 00:40:49.220
but leaving here...

757
00:40:50.590 --> 00:40:53.000
I know it's not
going to be for you.

758
00:40:54.670 --> 00:40:58.980
So please say your
goodbyes to everyone.

759
00:41:03.290 --> 00:41:04.960
Although I'm sad to go home.

760
00:41:05.020 --> 00:41:08.060
being in this house
has reminded me

761
00:41:08.060 --> 00:41:10.630
of the joy that
I bring to people's life.

762
00:41:10.630 --> 00:41:13.510
And regardless
of all the hurt.

763
00:41:13.540 --> 00:41:15.950
the heartache.
the pain. the losses.

764
00:41:15.950 --> 00:41:20.150
God has so much more
in store for me.

765
00:41:21.660 --> 00:41:23.330
- You did great.
- Thank you.

766
00:41:23.360 --> 00:41:26.970
I know it got emotional. but it
was wonderful to meet you.

767
00:41:26.970 --> 00:41:28.940
You did wonderful.

768
00:41:28.970 --> 00:41:31.280
- Bye. Damienne.
- Good luck. Damienne.

769
00:41:31.310 --> 00:41:32.780
- Love you!
- Love you!

770
00:41:32.810 --> 00:41:35.750
I love you!

771
00:41:37.690 --> 00:41:40.090
Look. eliminations
are always tough.

772
00:41:40.130 --> 00:41:43.100
but you are halfway
through the competition

773
00:41:43.100 --> 00:41:48.110
and so much closer to
one of you winning $200.000.

774
00:41:48.140 --> 00:41:50.150
We had a hell of a party.

775
00:41:50.150 --> 00:41:52.550
but please go get some rest

776
00:41:52.590 --> 00:41:54.560
because the next 24 hours

777
00:41:54.590 --> 00:41:56.560
are going to be pure hell

778
00:41:56.590 --> 00:41:58.100
and painful.

779
00:41:58.130 --> 00:42:01.970
I will see you at dawn.
Nighty-night.

780
00:42:01.970 --> 00:42:03.810
At the end of the day.
I'm glad I won.

781
00:42:03.840 --> 00:42:06.980
It sucks that
Damienne went home.

782
00:42:07.010 --> 00:42:08.980
but we just met
all these people.

783
00:42:09.020 --> 00:42:10.750
It's not like they're
lifelong friends with us.

784
00:42:10.820 --> 00:42:13.190
We don't know them.
It's like taking the trash out.

785
00:42:13.230 --> 00:42:14.760
Like. it doesn't affect me.

786
00:42:14.830 --> 00:42:16.900
I'm going to keep fighting.

787
00:42:19.810 --> 00:42:23.180
Zach can rot.
and I can't wait until this day

788
00:42:23.210 --> 00:42:24.750
that you leave the game.

789
00:42:24.820 --> 00:42:26.620
If it's anything
and everything I do.

790
00:42:26.620 --> 00:42:29.930
revenge will be made
for Damienne. I promise.

791
00:42:35.240 --> 00:42:37.880
Next time on "Fear Factor:
House Of Fear"...

792
00:42:37.910 --> 00:42:41.220
Welcome to the Pain Auction.

793
00:42:41.250 --> 00:42:44.250
a nonstop 24 hours of hell.

794
00:42:44.250 --> 00:42:45.620
Oh. my God.

795
00:42:45.620 --> 00:42:46.760
We're about to get hurt.

796
00:42:46.760 --> 00:42:48.400
Any of you could be eliminated.

797
00:42:48.460 --> 00:42:50.770
- What?
- Hot melted wax.

798
00:42:50.830 --> 00:42:55.110
biting snakes.
electricity. needles!

799
00:42:56.140 --> 00:42:59.020
This is a pie-eating contest.

800
00:42:59.020 --> 00:43:01.360
This is the last supper
from hell.

801
00:43:01.390 --> 00:43:04.760
I hope you came hungry.
Heh. heh. heh.

802
00:43:04.760 --> 00:43:06.160
Everyone's puking.
Oh. Lord.

